1
00:00:10,236 --> 00:00:12,336
When did you figure it out?

2
00:00:13,422 --> 00:00:16,229
- How did you know?
- Shut up.

3
00:00:18,682 --> 00:00:20,862
But how did you find out?

4
00:00:26,902 --> 00:00:28,517
Shut it.

5
00:00:39,069 --> 00:00:41,137
- Are you staying late?
- I'll be heading home soon.

6
00:00:41,137 --> 00:00:42,696
Lunch was so good today.

7
00:00:42,696 --> 00:00:44,322
Sir!

8
00:00:44,322 --> 00:00:46,489
Ah, Hyun Jae!

9
00:00:46,489 --> 00:00:48,022
Good afternoon, sir.

10
00:00:48,022 --> 00:00:49,448
Did you have lunch yet?

11
00:00:49,448 --> 00:00:51,496
I did, sir.

12
00:00:51,496 --> 00:00:53,141
Long time no see, Hyun Jae.

13
00:00:53,141 --> 00:00:54,789
- Producer Lee, sir.
- How have you been?

14
00:00:54,789 --> 00:00:56,069
Fine, sir.

15
00:00:56,069 --> 00:00:57,082
Good afternoon.

16
00:00:57,082 --> 00:01:00,276
Is this the first time you two are seeing
each other since the survival program?

17
00:01:00,276 --> 00:01:03,682
Oh, well... I guess it is.

18
00:01:03,682 --> 00:01:06,422
Hyun Jae. I heard you have an album
coming out by the end of the year.

19
00:01:06,422 --> 00:01:08,096
That's right, sir.

20
00:01:08,096 --> 00:01:12,489
So you're a proper artist now, aren't you?

21
00:01:13,383 --> 00:01:14,960
Hey, Hyun Jae.

22
00:01:15,589 --> 00:01:18,689
Be grateful to the CEO, you hear me?

23
00:01:20,496 --> 00:01:22,549
Hey, come on, now.

24
00:01:22,549 --> 00:01:25,523
He's doing wonderfully already.

25
00:01:25,523 --> 00:01:27,334
Hyun Jae!

26
00:01:28,609 --> 00:01:29,956
Good afternoon, sir.

27
00:01:29,956 --> 00:01:32,303
What? You're here as well?

28
00:01:32,303 --> 00:01:33,729
I am, sir.

29
00:01:33,729 --> 00:01:34,969
Unicorn.

30
00:01:34,969 --> 00:01:37,043
Oh, I remember.

31
00:01:37,043 --> 00:01:40,392
Right, you had a merger with Unicorn.

32
00:01:41,669 --> 00:01:44,969
Fate works in mysterious ways, isn't that so?

33
00:01:44,969 --> 00:01:47,976
You're pretty unfortunate.

34
00:01:51,123 --> 00:01:53,416
- Let's head inside, Producer Lee.
- All right.

35
00:02:00,863 --> 00:02:03,729
- I'm starving. Let's go.
- Okay.

36
00:02:19,276 --> 00:02:20,847
What's going on?

37
00:02:22,383 --> 00:02:24,043
What's with them?

38
00:02:24,043 --> 00:02:25,959
Jae Min!

39
00:02:31,069 --> 00:02:32,093
Now, look here.

40
00:02:32,093 --> 00:02:34,262
"Shin Jae Min, wrongly accused of stalking,

41
00:02:34,262 --> 00:02:36,837
is not who we all thought he was."

42
00:02:38,980 --> 00:02:41,554
I know you've been having a hard time.

43
00:02:41,554 --> 00:02:43,600
We've got your back now.

44
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:45,614
So do your best, too, Jae Min.

45
00:02:45,614 --> 00:02:46,979
Okay?

46
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:51,467
Hey, look at that.

47
00:02:51,467 --> 00:02:53,840
The internet loves you, too.

48
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:55,759
"Justice for Jae Min..."

49
00:02:55,759 --> 00:02:58,095
[You can see it in his face,
Jae Min didn't do anything wrong!]

50
00:02:59,207 --> 00:03:01,120
The press took pretty well to it, too.

51
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:02,714
Give it a good, clean ending, you hear?

52
00:03:02,714 --> 00:03:05,654
You know, like those stories about karma.

53
00:03:20,734 --> 00:03:23,225
It's a great song, don't you think?

54
00:03:31,343 --> 00:03:34,210
Well? It's good, right?

55
00:03:34,210 --> 00:03:37,097
- Yes, sir.
- See? I told you, didn't I?

56
00:03:37,097 --> 00:03:38,641
There's nothing this guy can't do.

57
00:03:38,641 --> 00:03:40,743
He's a genius. A genius!

58
00:03:40,743 --> 00:03:41,750
Thank you, sir.

59
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:43,470
Stop being so modest.

60
00:03:43,470 --> 00:03:46,423
I knew you had it in you from the start.

61
00:03:46,423 --> 00:03:49,417
All right, everyone. We'll start
practicing with this demo track for now.

62
00:03:49,417 --> 00:03:51,517
Anyone have any thoughts on this?

63
00:03:53,763 --> 00:03:54,937
All right.

64
00:03:54,937 --> 00:03:57,363
It's a good song, no doubt.

65
00:03:57,363 --> 00:04:00,423
Great, then, let's get it on, boys!

66
00:04:05,417 --> 00:04:07,710
Khun, you stay for a second.

67
00:04:07,710 --> 00:04:09,077
Well, you see...

68
00:04:09,077 --> 00:04:10,869
about the lyrics...

69
00:04:10,869 --> 00:04:13,962
Just translating everything in Korean isn't it.

70
00:04:13,962 --> 00:04:17,213
If it's all just Korean, Korean,
it's going to sound bland. Not to good taste.

71
00:04:17,213 --> 00:04:21,000
So get a good translator, give it some flavor.

72
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,667
It needs that zing, you see...

73
00:04:26,362 --> 00:04:29,522
- That was incredible.
- Just our style.

74
00:04:30,449 --> 00:04:33,116
I prefer my songs harder.

75
00:04:33,116 --> 00:04:34,882
It suits you perfectly, though.

76
00:04:34,882 --> 00:04:36,702
It's like it was written specifically for you.

77
00:04:36,702 --> 00:04:38,049
Really?

78
00:04:38,049 --> 00:04:39,269
I don't know about that.

79
00:04:39,269 --> 00:04:41,109
Oh, stop playing dumb.

80
00:04:41,109 --> 00:04:42,929
It hits you the second you hear it, right?

81
00:04:42,929 --> 00:04:44,509
That's your song.

82
00:04:44,509 --> 00:04:46,316
Is that so?

83
00:04:46,316 --> 00:04:49,009
Aw, look at Jae Min, all set up for success.

84
00:04:49,009 --> 00:04:51,206
Stop it, that's not true.

85
00:04:56,616 --> 00:04:58,023
What is it?

86
00:05:00,662 --> 00:05:02,762
Hey, Jae min.

87
00:05:05,696 --> 00:05:09,106
I'm sorry... for misjudging you.

88
00:05:10,482 --> 00:05:12,882
I'm sorry, too.

89
00:05:17,942 --> 00:05:21,076
Let bygones be bygones.

90
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:06,677
Hey, Khun.

91
00:06:07,540 --> 00:06:10,779
I'm sorry... about that time.

92
00:06:19,472 --> 00:06:22,852
If you're really sorry, bottoms up.

93
00:06:22,852 --> 00:06:24,106
Come on, there's no way.

94
00:06:24,106 --> 00:06:25,792
You Thai guys are a different breed!

95
00:06:25,792 --> 00:06:27,892
- Show us! Drink!
- Chug it, chug it!

96
00:06:27,892 --> 00:06:30,357
Bottoms up! Cheers!

97
00:06:30,357 --> 00:06:32,704
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

98
00:07:10,806 --> 00:07:12,519
Jae Min.

99
00:07:13,146 --> 00:07:14,606
That was good.

100
00:07:14,606 --> 00:07:16,135
Thank you, sir.

101
00:07:20,132 --> 00:07:21,719
Good job, everybody!

102
00:07:21,719 --> 00:07:23,510
You worked hard!

103
00:07:26,727 --> 00:07:29,074
Your team's having another get-together?

104
00:07:29,074 --> 00:07:32,014
I'm jealous of you guys.

105
00:07:32,014 --> 00:07:33,827
Where are you?

106
00:07:34,787 --> 00:07:36,887
Okay, don't overdo it.

107
00:07:45,620 --> 00:07:47,720
Get home safe.

108
00:07:55,887 --> 00:07:57,531
Do you...

109
00:07:58,627 --> 00:08:00,740
want to grab dinner with me?

110
00:08:03,294 --> 00:08:07,027
Khun must be at the get-together, so...

111
00:08:16,220 --> 00:08:18,642
I just got invited to hang out.

112
00:08:19,454 --> 00:08:21,408
I'm hanging up.

113
00:08:42,106 --> 00:08:43,772
[Wanna sneak out?]

114
00:08:55,535 --> 00:08:57,986
[Yoon Soo An, I said let's go!]

115
00:09:06,831 --> 00:09:08,931
I need to use the restroom.

116
00:09:22,005 --> 00:09:24,078
Huh? What are you doing here?

117
00:09:24,078 --> 00:09:25,731
I kept texting you.

118
00:09:25,731 --> 00:09:26,969
Why did you ignore them?

119
00:09:26,969 --> 00:09:28,602
You texted me?

120
00:09:29,771 --> 00:09:31,448
I didn't get any...

121
00:09:36,645 --> 00:09:38,698
[Block this number]

122
00:09:47,091 --> 00:09:48,705
Did you block my number?

123
00:09:48,705 --> 00:09:49,945
Wait, no, it's not like that.

124
00:09:49,945 --> 00:09:51,011
Give it back.

125
00:09:51,011 --> 00:09:52,926
- Give it back, now!
- Just wait.

126
00:09:52,926 --> 00:09:54,641
Wait, let me see.

127
00:10:00,438 --> 00:10:02,265
What is this?

128
00:10:02,265 --> 00:10:03,837
What do you mean?

129
00:10:05,751 --> 00:10:06,776
This text.

130
00:10:06,776 --> 00:10:08,233
[I miss you, Hyun Jae. Don't you miss me?]

131
00:10:10,458 --> 00:10:12,659
Did you send this to me?

132
00:10:14,898 --> 00:10:16,811
You left me on read, remember?

133
00:10:16,811 --> 00:10:18,411
Or do you, what,

134
00:10:18,411 --> 00:10:20,511
feel sorry for me?

135
00:10:21,138 --> 00:10:23,018
It's fine now.

136
00:10:23,638 --> 00:10:25,365
No, it's not that.

137
00:10:25,365 --> 00:10:27,485
I never got this text.

138
00:10:27,485 --> 00:10:29,665
I've never seen it before.

139
00:10:29,665 --> 00:10:31,575
That makes no sense.

140
00:10:39,891 --> 00:10:40,891
What is it?

141
00:10:40,891 --> 00:10:42,737
Is something wrong?

142
00:10:45,019 --> 00:10:46,625
This is the day...

143
00:10:46,625 --> 00:10:48,725
they took my phone away.

144
00:10:55,591 --> 00:10:57,238
I'm sorry.

145
00:10:57,238 --> 00:10:59,338
For not clearing it up sooner.

146
00:11:00,511 --> 00:11:03,611
Don't apologize. It's not your fault.

147
00:11:06,685 --> 00:11:08,117
Okay?

148
00:11:09,211 --> 00:11:11,858
It's all water under the bridge now.

149
00:11:11,858 --> 00:11:13,879
Let's just move forward.

150
00:11:14,498 --> 00:11:16,747
I like how things are right now.

151
00:11:23,191 --> 00:11:24,909
Then...

152
00:11:26,338 --> 00:11:28,438
That text...

153
00:11:30,831 --> 00:11:33,076
Can I give you my answer now?

154
00:13:30,745 --> 00:13:36,735
[CEO Goo Sang Cheol]

155
00:13:42,364 --> 00:13:44,032
Kim Hyun Jae.

156
00:13:44,032 --> 00:13:46,532
Want to hear something funny?

157
00:13:48,832 --> 00:13:50,159
Failed yet again.

158
00:13:50,159 --> 00:13:52,312
What? Why are you looking at me like that?

159
00:13:52,312 --> 00:13:53,291
What's this?

160
00:13:53,291 --> 00:13:55,244
[Il Woo, why aren't you answering?]
Il Woo disclosed the texts and calls,

161
00:13:55,244 --> 00:13:56,932
and they're taking legal action.

162
00:13:56,932 --> 00:14:00,385
These texts were fabricated
and bent to fit their agenda.

163
00:14:00,385 --> 00:14:03,465
We should put out our own side of the story
and take legal action...

164
00:14:04,119 --> 00:14:05,672
Manager Park.

165
00:14:05,672 --> 00:14:08,732
Why do you think I picked Jae Min?
